C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cbf9830b651c00193a308c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3Cp%3EJeff%20Swensen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETrump's%20attorneys%20unsuccessfully%20sought%20to%20move%20the%20federal%20election%20interference%20trial%20to%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHis%20team%20cited%20%3Cem%3EPowell%20v.%20Alabama%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20that%20guarantees%20a%20defendant%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20time%26quot%3B%20to%20obtain%20counsel.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHarvard%20professor%20Dehlia%20Umunna%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20Trump%20team%20citing%20the%20%26quot%3BScottsboro%20Boys%26quot%3B%20case%20was%20%26quot%3Bunbelievably%20juvenile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EWhen%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20attorneys%20sought%20to%20push%20the%20ex-president's%20federal%20election%20interference%20trial%20to%20April%202026%2C%20they%20cited%20the%20landmark%20Supreme%20Court%20case%20regarding%20the%20infamous%20convictions%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BScottsboro%20Boys%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20nine%20young%20Black%20men%20falsly%20accused%20of%20raping%20two%20white%20women.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EIn%20the%201932%20decision%2C%20Powell%20v.%20Alabama%2C%C2%A0the%20court's%20ruling%20guaranteed%20the%20right%20of%20a%20defendant%20to%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20time%20and%20opportunity%20to%20secure%20counsel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20Scottsboro%20case%20attracted%20widespread%20attention.%20The%20men%20were%20swiftly%20arrested%2C%20tried%2C%20and%20sentenced%20within%20weeks%2C%20with%20hardly%20had%20any%20opportunity%20to%20speak%20with%20their%20attorneys%20before%20their%20convictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20Powell%2C%20the%20men%20had%20their%20convictions%20reversed%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20accusations%20didn't%20go%20away.%20Collectively%2C%20the%20men%20had%20spent%20decades%20in%20prison.%20By%201950%2C%20some%20battled%20declining%20health%20and%20violence.%20One%20of%20the%20men%20died%20by%20suicide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3ETrump's%20legal%20team%2C%20in%20seeking%20to%20fight%20charges%20that%20Trump%20sought%20to%20subvert%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%20results%2C%20argued%20that%20that%20the%20former%20president%20needed%20additional%20time%20to%20prepare%20a%20defense%2C%20pointing%20to%20%3Cem%3EPowell.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20Tanya%20Chutkan%20wasn't%20persuaded%20by%20the%20citation%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-election-interference-trial-super-tuesday-federal-court-start-date-2023-8%5C%22%3Eset%20the%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20begin%20in%20March%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20many%20cases%20unduly%20delayed%20because%20a%20defendant%20lacks%20adequate%20representation%20or%20cannot%20properly%20review%20discovery%20because%20they%20are%20detained%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20the%20case%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EChutkan%20said%20that%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20not%20been%20jailed%20for%20any%20extensive%20period%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bprofoundly%20different%26quot%3B%20situation%20that%20what%20was%20outlined%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPowell.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EDehlia%20Umunna%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Law%20School%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fhistory%2F2023%2F09%2F02%2Fscottsboro-boys-trump-election-case%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bunbelievably%20juvenile%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Trump%20team%20to%20cite%20the%20Scottsboro%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20there%20was%20an%20explicit%20denial%20of%20due%20process%20because%20the%20Scottsboro%20defendants%20were%20not%20afforded%20reasonable%20time%20and%20opportunity%20to%20procure%20counsel%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20newspaper.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20the%20case%20with%20defendant%20Trump.%20His%20actions%20leading%20to%20these%20charges%20occurred%20over%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20he%20has%20several%20lawyers%20representing%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EKenneth%20W.%20Mack%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20and%20an%20affiliate%20professor%20of%20history%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20Scottsboro%20case%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20landmarks%20of%20American%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20actually%20thought%20that%20citing%20it%2