ikely.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20classic%20definition%20of%20air%20superiority%20comes%20down%20a%20simple%20proposition%3A%20Your%20air%20force%20can%20conduct%20its%20assigned%20missions%20while%20keeping%20an%20enemy%20air%20force%20from%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20grappling%20with%20the%20realization%20that%20control%20of%20the%20skies%20doesn't%20mean%20what%20it%20used%20to.%20Strategists%20on%20both%20sides%20are%20wondering%20whether%20it's%20even%20possible%20to%20achieve%20aerial%20dominance%20for%20more%20than%20brief%20periods%20against%20near-peer%20adversaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20think%20about%20it%20temporally%2C%26quot%3B%20Clinton%20Hinote%2C%20who%20retired%20from%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20as%20a%20lieutenant%20general%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20said%20during%20a%20recent%20Aviation%20Week%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faviationweek.com%2Fpodcasts%2Fcheck-6%2Fpodcast-understanding-air-power-former-usaf-futurist%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20organize%20your%20force%20to%20create%20superiority%20so%20that%20you%20can%20do%20something%20and%20then%20you'll%20retreat%20back%20or%20try%20to%20regroup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20a%20struggle%20back%20and%20forth%20for%20air%20superiority%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Hinote%2C%20whose%20last%20position%20was%20as%20the%20Air%20Force's%20chief%20futurist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20KC-135%20refuels%20F-22s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f221431b7ced0019c6dc09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Air%20Force%20KC-135%20refuels%20F-22s%20over%20the%20Atlantic%20in%20April%202018.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Carlin%20Leslie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20different%20degrees%20of%20aerial%20dominance.%20The%20most%20comprehensive%20is%20air%20supremacy%2C%20which%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.doctrine.af.mil%2FPortals%2F61%2Fdocuments%2Fdoctrine_updates%2Fdu_17_01.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefines%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20when%20%26quot%3Bthe%20opposing%20force%20is%20incapable%20of%20effective%20interference%20within%20the%20operational%20area%20using%20air%20and%20missile%20threats.%26quot%3B%20It%20describes%20the%20sort%20of%20environment%20enjoyed%20by%20American%20airpower%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20level%20is%20air%20superiority%2C%20which%20the%20Air%20Force%20defines%20as%20%26quot%3Bcontrol%20of%20the%20air%20by%20one%20force%20that%20permits%20the%20conduct%20of%20its%20operations%20at%20a%20given%20time%20and%20place%20without%20prohibitive%20interference%20from%20air%20and%20missile%20threats.%26quot%3B%20Think%20of%20the%20invasion%20of%20Normandy%20in%201944%2C%20where%20the%20Luftwaffe%20was%20more%20of%20a%20nuisance%20than%20threat%2C%20or%20of%20Vietnam%2C%20where%20the%20massive%20US%20bombing%20campaign%20was%20impeded%20but%20never%20halted%20by%20North%20Vietnamese%20MiGs%20and%20anti-aircraft%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20concepts%20date%20to%20the%201920s%20and%20the%20Italian%20airpower%20theorist%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Farticle%2F0411douhet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGiulio%20Douhet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20air%20forces%20should%20be%20independent%20rather%20than%20part%20of%20armies%2C%20as%20was%20common%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouhet%20also%20believed%20that%20strategic%20bombing%20alone%20could%20win%20wars%20by%20destroying%20enemy%20cities%2C%20which%20would%20paralyze%20the%20economy%20and%20collapse%20civilian%20morale.%20Doing%20that%20required%20preventing%20the%20enemy%20from%20using%20its%20airpower%20in%20the%20same%20way.%20%26quot%3BThe%20one%20effective%20method%20of%20defending%20one's%20own%20territory%20from%20an%20offensive%20by%20air%20is%20to%20destroy%20the%20enemy's%20air%20power%20with%20the%20greatest%20possible%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20Douhet%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22B-17%20bombers%20over%20Germany%20during%20WWII%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6204325e3b86990018b29f07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Army%20Air%20Force%20B-17s%20bomb%20an%20aircraft%20factory%20in%20eastern%20Germany%20during%20World%20War%20II.%3Cp%3Eullstein%20bild%2Fullstein%20bild%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDouhet's%20theories%20on%20strategic%20bombardment%20proved%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20neither%20Germany%2C%20Japan%2C%20nor%20North%20Vietnam%20sued%20for%20peace%20because%20of%20bombing%20%E2%80%94%20but%20his%20notion%20of%20control%20of%20the%20air%20lived%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20bomber%20raids%20over%20Germany%20in%201944%20were%20designed%20to%20lure%20the%20Luftwaffe's%20fighter%20force%20into%20the%20air%2C%20where%20they%20could%20be%20destroyed%20by%20American%20fighters.%20The%20spectacular%20Israeli%20victory%20in%201967%20was%20preceded%20by%20a%20surprise%20aerial%20assault%20that%20destroyed%20the%20Arab%20air%20forces%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20enabling%20Israeli%20ground%20troops%20to%20receive%20constant%20air%20support%20without%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20remarkable%20about%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-general-surprised-russian-failure-against-ukraine-soviet-era-defenses-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20limited%20impact%20of%20airpower%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Despite%20the%20presence%20of%20advanced%20jets%2C%20especially%20on%20the%20Russian%20side%2C%20both%20air%20forces%20are%20flying%20cautiously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountries-are-giving-ukraine-air-defenses-for-russian-missiles-drones-2022-11%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20face%20of%20surface-to-air%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20the%20Soviet-designed%20S-300%20or%20newer%20Western-made%20air%20defenses.%20Drones%20have%20more%20freedom%20to%20operate%2C%20but%20even%20those%20face%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.rusi.org%2F403-SR-Russian-Tactics-web-final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20losses%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20physical%20and%20electronic%20countermeasures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20military%20is%20also%20wondering%20whether%20it's%20even%20feasible%20to%20control%20the%20skies%20permanently%20during%20a%20conflict%20between%20forces%20with%20comparable%20numbers%20of%20long-range%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China%20air%20force%20J-10%20fighter%20jet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f224191b7ced0019c6e0dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221306%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Chinese%20J-10%20fighter%20jet%20at%20the%20Zhuhai%20Air%20Show%20Center%20in%20November%202022.%3Cp%3EZhou%20Guoqiang%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20ability%20of%20such%20forces%20to%20deny%20each%20other%20control%20of%20the%20air%2C%20the%20goal%20should%20shift%20from%20control%20at%20%26quot%3Ball%20times%20over%20all%20areas%26quot%3B%20to%20pursuing%20%26quot%3Bair%20superiority%20for%20key%20tasks%20at%20key%20times%20and%20over%20key%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20three%20authors%20affiliated%20with%20the%20China's%20Air%20Force%20Command%20College%20wrote%20in%20the%20Chinese%20military's%20official%20newspaper%20this%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Chinese%20critics%20point%20out%20that%20a%20variety%20of%20new%20systems%2C%20including%20drones%20and%20cyberwarfare%2C%20will%20vastly%20complicate%20any%20quest%20for%20aerial%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20PLA%20is%20clearly%20refuting%20the%20feasibility%20and%20the%20necessity%20of%20achieving%20command%20of%20the%20air%20as%20Douhet%20originally%20conceived%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Derek%20Solen%2C%20a%20researcher%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force's%20China%20Aerospace%20Studies%20Institute%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20July%20article%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamestown.org%2Fprogram%2Fthe-pla-reconceptualizes-control-of-the-air%2F%3Fmc_cid%3D80b4a05e41%26mc_eid%3D3b082b853a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJamestown%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20conceptual%20change%20has%20two%20implications%2C%26quot%3B%20Solen%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20the%20PLA%20will%20seek%20absolute%20control%20of%20the%20air%20in%20future%20campaigns%20such%20as%20an%20invasion%20of%20Taiwan.%20Second%2C%20the%20PLA%20will%20likely%20reduce%20its%20spatial%20and%20temporal%20requirements%20for%20control%20of%20the%20air%20as%20its%20capabilities%20to%20conduct%20multi-domain%20operations%20improve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chinese%20air%20force%20J-20%20stealth%20fighter%20jet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f224181e6afd00196a4cf1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChinese%20J-20%20stealth%20fighter%20jets%20train%20in%20Guangdong%20in%20November%202022.%3Cp%3EYu%20Hongchun%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20both%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20moving%20away%20from%20a%20single-minded%20focus%20on%20air%20combat%20and%20emphasizing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foverthehorizonmdos.wpcomstaging.com%2F2018%2F09%2F17%2Fdefining-the-domain-in-multi-domain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emulti-domain%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20loosely%20defined%20concept%20that%20includes%20land%2C%20air%2C%20sea%2C%20space%2C%20cyberwarfare%2C%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%2C%20and%20information%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20operate%20across%20those%20domains%20%26quot%3Ballows%20you%20to%20not%20think%20of%20the%20symmetric%20fight%20in%20the%20air%20where%20you%20just%20have%20fighter%20airplanes%26quot%3B%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20after%20it%26quot%3B%20against%20other%20fighters%2C%20Hinote%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20still%20important%20that%20we%20can%20do%20that%2C%20but%20if%20you%20can%20use%20other%20domains%20to%20establish%20air%20superiority%20and%20to%20attack%20the%20adversary's%20use%20of%20the%20air%2C%20that's%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20ground%20troops%20haven't%20faced%20attacks%20from%20enemy%20aircraft%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2FPDF%2FMagazineArchive%2FDocuments%2F2011%2FJune%25202011%2F0611april.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20the%20Korean%20War%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20future%20where%20that%20kind%20of%20air%20dominance%20can't%20be%20achieved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-iraq-ballistic-missile-attack-us-troops-traumatic-brain-injury-2023-8%5C%22%3Ewould%20seem%20to%20be%20a%20major%20threat%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20way%20America%20wages%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20however%2C%20Hinote%20believes%20a%20lack%20of%20air%20supremacy%20might%20not%20be%20so%20terrible%20when%20fending%20off%20an%20attack%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20or%20a%20Chinese%20invasion%20of%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20as%20we%20think%20about%20this%20idea%20of%20denial%2C%20even%20a%20sta