ot%3B%20the%20third-term%20congresswoman%20told%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOcasio-Cortez%20was%20part%20of%20a%20congressional%20delegation%20that%20recently%20traveled%20to%20the%20region.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%20said%20in%20a%20newly-published%20interview%20that%20the%20US%20government%20needed%20to%20apologize%20for%20its%20history%20of%20interventions%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20arguing%20that%20such%20actions%20contributed%20to%20government%20instability%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2023%2Fsep%2F02%2Faoc-us-apology-latin-america-coup-chile%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Democrat%20%E2%80%94%20who%20returned%20from%20Chile%20just%20days%20before%20the%2050th%20anniversary%20of%20the%201973%20Chilean%20coup%20d'%C3%A9tat%2C%20where%20the%20democratic%20socialist%20president%20Salvador%20Allende%20was%20ousted%20from%20power%20%E2%80%94%20spoke%20in%20detail%20regarding%20America's%20role%20in%20the%20region%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20US%20needed%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20past%20mistakes%20in%20order%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20more%20productive%20diplomatic%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20we%20owe%20Chile%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-link-name%3D%5C%22in%20body%20link%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Fchile%5C%22%20data-component%3D%5C%22auto-linked-tag%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20just%20Chile%20but%20many%20aspects%20of%20that%20region%2C%20an%20apology%2C%26quot%3B%20Ocasio-Cortez%20told%20the%20publication.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20apology%20indicates%20weakness%3B%20I%20think%20it%20indicates%20a%20desire%20to%20meet%20our%20hemispheric%20partners%20with%20respect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20hard%20for%20us%20to%20move%20forward%20when%20there%20is%20this%20huge%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20trust%20due%20to%20that%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThe%20first%20step%20around%20that%20is%20acknowledgement%20and%20saying%20we%20want%20to%20approach%20this%20region%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20mutual%20respect%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20new%20and%20it's%20historic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20generations%2C%20the%20US%20has%20had%20an%20outsized%20role%20in%20seeking%20to%20oust%20socialist%20governments%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20played%20a%20role%20in%20coups%20that%20led%20to%20the%20ousters%20of%20Guatemalan%20president%20Jacobo%20%C3%81rbenz%20and%20Brazilian%20president%20Jo%C3%A3o%20Goulart%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20and%20American%20leaders%20had%20long%20sought%20to%20remove%20former%20Cuban%20president%20Fidel%20Castro%20from%20power.%20(Castro%20served%20as%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Cuba%20from%201959%20to%201976%20and%20was%20the%20country's%20president%20from%201976%20to%202008.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOcasio-Cortez%20told%20The%20Guardian%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20the%20US%20reflect%20on%20its%20previous%20decisions%20to%20overthrow%20governments%20that%20it%20saw%20as%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLatin%20America%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20due%20to%20its%20proximity%2C%20was%20absolutely%20unique%20in%20US%20interventionism%20during%20the%20cold%20war%2C%20and%20that%20was%20under%20%5Bsecretary%20of%20state%5D%20Henry%20Kissinger%20and%20President%20Nixon%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20congresswoman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20Latin%20America%20is%20still%20very%20much%20grappling%20in%20the%20present%20day%20with%20the%20consequences%20of%20coups%20that%20were%20supported%20by%20the%20United%20States%2C%20with%20Operation%20Condor%20that%20Henry%20Kissinger%20helped%20largely%20lead%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20see%20is%20the%20ramifications%20of%20decades%20of%20those%20policies%20and%20how%20they%20shape%20US-Latin%20American%20relations%20today%2C%20I%20think%20primarily%20around%20trust.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOcasio-Cortez%20was%20part%20of%20a%20congressional%20delegation%20that%20recently%20traveled%20to%20Brazil%20and%20Colombia%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20Chile%2C%20with%20a%20goal%20of%20forging%20a%20more%20positive%20relationship%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20sending%20a%20message%20not%20of%20paternalism%20or%20consequences%20or%20telling%20people%20what%20to%20do%2C%20but%20truly%20saying%20we're%20here%20to%20reset%20this%20relationship%20in%20a%20new%20light%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOcasio-Cortez%20has%20sought%20to%20declassify%20information%20that%20might%20offer%20more%20insight%20into%20the%20CIA's%20role%20in%20the%201973%20Chilean%20coup%2C%20which%20ushered%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F07%2F30%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fpinochet-banco-de-chile.html%5C%22%3Ebrutal%20regime%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Augusto%20Pinochet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20element%20of%20it%20is%20just%20acknowledgement%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20even%20at%20the%20point%20of%20an%20apology%20because%20we%20haven't%20even%20gotten%20to%20an%20acknowledgement%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20I%20believe%20the%20declassification%20of%20these%20documents%20is%20going%20to%20be%20so%20critical%20to%20our%20relationship%20to%20Chile%2C%20as%20well%20as%20also%20acknowledging%20the%20unified%20right-wing%20movements%20that%20the%20US%20has%20very%20much%20historically%20been%20exporting%20to%20Latin%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-latin-america-us-government-apologize-interventions-coups-region-20