%20skull%20may%20challenge%20the%20long-held%20belief%20that%20the%20ancestors%20of%20apes%20and%20humans%20came%20from%20Africa%2C%20a%20controversial%20new%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20partial%20skull%20of%20the%20ape%2C%20called%20an%20Anadoluvius%20turkae%2C%20was%20found%20in%20Cankiri%2C%20Turkey%2C%20and%20appears%20to%20date%20back%20to%208.7%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Farchaeology%2Fhuman-and-ape-ancestors-arose-in-europe-not-in-africa-controversial-study-claims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20early%20hominins%2C%20which%20include%20humans%2C%20the%20African%20apes%2C%20and%20their%20fossil%20ancestors%2C%20are%20not%20seen%20in%20Africa%20until%20around%20seven%20million%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20challenges%20the%20widely-held%20view%20that%20the%20ancestors%20of%20African%20apes%20and%20humans%20originated%20exclusively%20in%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20say%20that%20this%20suggests%20that%20hominins%20might%20have%20first%20evolved%20in%20Europe%20before%20migrating%20to%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221110%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20skull%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f4b6c5781926001910b37c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20skull.%3Cp%3ESevim-Erol%2C%20A.%2C%20Begun%2C%20D.R.%2C%20S%C3%B6zer%2C%20%C3%87.S.%20et%20al.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20findings%20further%20suggest%20that%20hominins%20not%20only%20evolved%20in%20western%20and%20central%20Europe%20but%20spent%20over%20five%20million%20years%20evolving%20there%20and%20spreading%20to%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20before%20eventually%20dispersing%20into%20Africa%2C%20probably%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20changing%20environments%20and%20diminishing%20forests%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Professor%20David%20Begun%2C%20a%20paleoanthropologist%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20and%20co-senior%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2F03%2Fdiscovery-of-87m-year-old-ape-rewrites-story-of-humanity%2F%3Fli_source%3DLI%26li_medium%3Dliftigniter-rhr%5C%22%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20new%20evidence%20supports%20the%20hypothesis%20that%20hominins%20originated%20in%20Europe%20and%20dispersed%20into%20Africa%20along%20with%20many%20other%20mammals%20between%20nine%20and%20seven%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20though%20it%20does%20not%20definitively%20prove%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20prove%20this%2C%20more%20fossils%20from%20Europe%20and%20Africa%20would%20need%20to%20be%20found%20from%20between%20seven%20and%20eight%20million%20years%20ago%20to%20try%20and%20find%20a%20link%20between%20the%20two%20groups%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%20suggested%20that%20the%20ape%20would%20have%20weighed%20around%20110%20to%20130%20pounds%2C%20possibly%20lived%20in%20a%20dry%20forest%2C%20and%20likely%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20skull%20was%20found%20in%202015%20but%20its%20significance%20was%20discussed%20in%20research%20recently%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Communications%20Biology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20researchers%20have%20said%20that%20the%20findings%20do%20not%20challenge%20our%20understanding%20of%20the%20origins%20of%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20has%20been%20a%20long-running%20debate%20regarding%20great%20ape%20and%20our%20origins%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Professor%20Chris%20Stringer%2C%20research%20leader%20in%20human%20evolution%20at%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20in%20London%2C%20The%20Telegraph%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20this%20find%20changes%20much%20from%20the%20discussions%20(