e-g20-summit%2Farticleshow%2F95492327.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBrazil%20was%20represented%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20the%20foreign%20minister-level%20as%20it%20was%20in%20the%20transition%20period%20after%20its%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20background%20brief%20also%20listed%20the%20country-wise%20details%20of%20who%20had%20attended%20summits%20at%20which%20level%20over%20the%20years.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20has%20not%20attended%20nine%20out%20of%20the%2016%20summit%20at%20the%20leadership%20level.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20things%20do%20not%20reflect%20anything%20about%20the%20host%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20background%20brief.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693676417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16203251%2FDelhi-G20.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-leader-dropouts-preemptive%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20official%20sources%20issued%20a%20long%20background%20brief%20to%20point%20out%20that%20skipping%20G-20%20summits%20is%20not%20an%20uncommon%20trait.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-leader-dropouts-preemptive%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Panel%20on%20'One%20Election'%20to%20Examine%20if%20%E2%80%98Ratification%20by%20States%E2%80%99%20Is%20Needed%2C%20Adhir%20Declines%20to%20Be%20on%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F25204736%2FScreen-Shot-2020-01-25-at-8.47.13-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20has%20notified%20an%20eight-member%20high-level%20committee%20to%20find%20a%20way%20of%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9Cholding%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20(Lok%20Sabha)%2C%20State%20Legislative%20Assemblies%2C%20Municipalities%20and%20Panchayats%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20framing%20of%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fegazette.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2F2023%2F248519.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterms%20and%20references%3C%2Fa%3E%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20government%20is%20keen%20to%20push%20the%20proposal%20for%20simultaneous%20polls%20unilaterally%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%20through%20a%20vote%20in%20parliament%2C%20where%20it%20has%20a%20comfortable%20majority%20%E2%80%93%20rather%20than%20with%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20states%20even%20though%20such%20a%20decision%20has%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20the%20latter%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%20(b)%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98terms%20and%20references%E2%80%99%20says%20the%20committee%20will%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%20and%20recommend%2C%20if%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20Constitution%20would%20require%20ratification%20by%20the%20States.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20committee%20and%20Adhir%E2%80%99s%20refusal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20has%20been%20appointed%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee.%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20Congress%20parliamentary%20party%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20former%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20former%20finance%20commission%20chairman%20N.K.%20Singh%2C%20former%20secretary%20general%20Lok%20Sabha%20Subhash%20C.%20Kashyap%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari%20are%20the%20other%20members.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20committee%20could%20raise%20eyebrows%20as%20almost%20all%20its%20members%20except%20Chowdhury%20are%20either%20BJP%20members%20or%20people%20who%20have%20been%20working%20with%20or%20have%20previously%20worked%20with%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Leaders%20of%20regional%20parties%2C%20who%20may%20be%20the%20most%20affected%20by%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20have%20also%20been%20ignored.%20Former%20and%20current%20election%20commissioners%2C%20who%20may%20be%20the%20best%20placed%20to%20point%20out%20logistical%20problems%20with%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20also%20do%20not%20figure%20in%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20the%20notification%2C%20Chowdhury%20declined%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%208-member%20committee%2C%20writing%20to%20Shah%2C%20saying%20he%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20exercise%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctotal%20eyewash.%E2%80%9D%20He%20wrote%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterms%20of%20reference%20have%20been%20prepared%20in%20a%20manner%20to%20guarantee%20its%20conclusions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20termed%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Csudden%20attempt%20to%20thrust%20a%20constitutionally%20suspect%2C%20pragmatically%20non-feasible%20and%20logically%20unimplementable%20idea%20on%20the%20nation%2C%20months%20before%20the%20general%20election%2C%20raising%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20ulterior%20motives%20of%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20he%20found%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20exclusion%20of%20the%20current%20LoP%20from%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%5BCongress%20President%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%5D%20a%20deliberate%20insult%20to%20the%20system%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20has%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20noting%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20former%20Congress%20Rajya%20Sabha%20leader%20of%20opposition%2C%20Ghulam%20Nadi%20Azad%20instead%20of%20the%20current%20Congress%20Rajya%20Sabha%20leader%20of%20opposition%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%20attempt%20to%20sabotage%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20believe%20that%20the%20High%20Level%20Committee%20on%20Simultaneous%20Elections%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20systematic%20attempt%20to%20sabotage%20India's%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20shocking%20insult%20to%20Parliament%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20appointed%20a%20former%20LOP%20to%20the%20Committee%20instead%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%20LOP%20Sh.%20Mallikarjun%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20K%20C%20Venugopal%20(%40kcvenugopalmp)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkcvenugopalmp%2Fstatus%2F1697998930665943162%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%202%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20high-level%20committee%20will%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%20and%20make%20recommendations%20for%20holding%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20municipalities%20and%20panchayats%2C%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20existing%20framework%20under%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20and%20other%20statutory%20provisions%2C%20and%20for%20that%20purpose%2C%20examine%20and%20recommend%20specific%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201950%2C%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20and%20the%20rules%20made%20thereunder%20and%20any%20other%20law%20or%20rules%20which%20would%20require%20amendments%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20holding%20simultaneous%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20has%20been%20asked%20to%20analyse%20and%20recommend%20possible%20solutions%20if%20there%20are%20scenarios%20like%20a%20hung%20house%2C%20adoption%20of%20no-confidence%20motion%20or%20defection.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20will%20examine%20the%20logistics%20and%20manpower%20required%2C%20including%20EVMs%2C%20VVPATs%2C%20etc%2C%20for%20holding%20such%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20notification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20notification%20also%20says%20that%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20will%20attend%20the%20committee%20meetings%20as%20a%20special%20invitee.%20The%20committee%20is%20expected%20to%20begin%20functioning%20immediately%20and%20submit%20its%20recommendations%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20earliest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservers%20have%20wondered%20on%20the%20appropriateness%20of%20the%20law%20ministry%20notifying%20this%20with%20Amit%20Shah%20finding%20a%20place%20on%20the%20committee%2C%20with%20Meghwal%20only%20present%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20invitee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20record%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20federal%20structure%20is%20questionable%2C%20with%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20happening%20with%20the%20parliament%20arrogating%20to%20itself%20the%20powers%20vested%20in%20the%20(then%20dissolved)%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%20assembly.%20In%20an%20unprecedented%20move%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20a%20state%20was%20bifurcated%20and%20demoted%20to%20a%20Union%20Territory%20without%20its%20views%20being%20taken%20into%20account.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20Delhi%2C%20the%20recent%20monsoon%20session%20of%20parliament%20witnessed%20an%20uproar%20after%20the%20government%20tabled%20a%20Bill%C2%A0%20for%20control%20of%20services%20and%20officers%E2%80%99%20posting%20in%20Delhi%2C%20with%20most%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties%20against%20the%20move.%20This%2C%20despite%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20making%20clear%20its%20views%20on%20an%20earlier%20ordinance%20brought%20by%20the%20union%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FImages%2Fpdf1%2FPart20.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%20368(2)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20deals%20with%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20needing%20ratification%20by%20states.%20It%20reads%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CProvided%20that%20if%20such%20amendment%20seeks%20to%20make%20any%20change%20in%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(a)%20article%2054%2C%20article%2055%2C%20article%2073%2C%20article%20162%20or%20article%20241%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(b)%20Chapter%20IV%20of%20Part%20V%2C%20Chapter%20V%20of%20Part%20VI%2C%20or%20Chapter%20I%20of%20Part%20XI%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(c)%20any%20of%20the%20Lists%20in%20the%20Seventh%20Schedule%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(d)%20the%20representation%20of%20States%20in%20Parliament%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(e)%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20article%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20amendment%20shall%20also%20require%20to%20be%20ratified%20by%20the%20Legislatures%20of%20not%20less%20than%20one-half%20of%20the%20States%20by%20resolutions%20to%20that%20effect%20passed%20by%20those%20Legislatures%20before%20the%20Bill%20making%20provision%20for%20such%20amendment%20is%20presented%20to%20the%20President%20for%20assent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20has%20been%20updated%20since%20publication%20with%20news%20on%20Adhir%20Chowdhury%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20be%20on%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693670669000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F25204736%2FScreen-Shot-2020-01-25-at-8.47.13-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20controversial%20proposal%20in%20the%20terms%20and%20references%20would%20be%20apiece%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20dismal%20track%20record%20on%20federalism%20or%20even%20just%20for%20consultation%20with%20the%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nobel%20foundation%20withdraws%20Russia%2C%20Belarus%20and%20Iran%20invitations%20after%20'strong%20reactions'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693669200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F768x432%2Fskynews-nobel-oslo-norway_6270127.jpg%3F20230901104501%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnobel-foundation-withdraws-invitation-for-russia-belarus-and-iran-representatives-12953328%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Nobel%20Foundation%20has%20withdrawn%20its%20invitation%20to%20representatives%20from%20Russia%2C%20Belarus%2C%20and%20Iran%20to%20attend%20this%20year's%20Nobel%20Prize%20award%20ceremonies%20after%20the%20controversial%20decision%20%26quot%3Bprovoked%20strong%20reactions%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnobel-foundation-withdraws-invitation-for-russia-belarus-and-iran-representatives-12953328%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnobel-foundation-withdraws-invitation-for-russia-belarus-and-iran-representatives-12953328%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnobel-foundation-withdraws-invitation-for-russia-belarus-and-iran-representatives-12953328%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Internet%20Ban%20a%20Mistake%2C%20During%20Conflict%20Manipur%20Media%20Was%20'Meitei%20Media'%3A%20EGI%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25122407%2FF4M3tHNWUAAGBhf.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20fact-finding%20team%20of%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20which%20visited%20Manipur%20to%20examine%20the%20media%20reportage%20in%20the%20state%2C%20has%20released%20a%20report%20in%20which%20it%20has%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cone-sided%E2%80%9D%20reports%20were%20published%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20and%20that%20the%20internet%20ban%20made%20%E2%80%9Cmatters%20worse%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20three-member%20team%20comprising%20Seema%20Guha%2C%20Bharat%20Bhushan%20and%20Sanjay%20Kapoor%20were%20in%20the%20state%20from%20August%207%20to%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%2024-page%20%E2%80%98Report%20of%20the%20fact-finding%20mission%20on%20media%E2%80%99s%20reportage%20of%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%E2%80%99%20also%20notes%20how%20certain%20media%20practices%20led%20to%20the%20vilification%20of%20the%20security%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%20its%20recommendations%2C%20it%20noted%3A%20%E2%80%9CMeitei%20media%20became%20a%20party%20to%20the%20vili%20fication%20of%20the%20security%20forces%2C%20especially%20the%20Assam%20Rifles.%20It%20failed%20in%20its%20duty%20by%20constant%20propaganda%20against%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%20claiming%20that%20it%20was%20only%20purveying%20the%20views%20of%20the%20public.%20It%20failed%20to%20verify%20the%20facts%2C%20weigh%20them%20and%20then%20use%20them%20in%20its%20reportage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20also%20tacitly%20supported%20this%20vili%20cation%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-assam-rifles-for-allowing-kuki-militants-to-flee%5C%22%3Eallowing%20Manipur%20Police%20to%20file%20an%20FIR%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%2C%20%E2%80%9Csuggesting%20that%20one%20hand%20of%20the%20state%20did%20not%20know%20what%20the%20other%20what%20the%20other%20was%20doing%20or%20this%20was%20deliberate%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20between%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20oldest%20paramilitary%20forces%2C%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%2C%20and%20Manipur%20police%20has%20been%20unprecedented.%20The%20Manipur%20Police%E2%80%99s%20FIR%20against%20it%20was%20ostensibly%20for%20%E2%80%9Callowing%20Kuki%20Militants%20to%20flee%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20The%20director%20general%20of%20Assam%20Rifles%2C%20Lt%20General%20P.C.%20Nair%2C%20on%20September%201%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fassam-rifles-dg-manipur-situation-unprecedented%5C%22%3Ethat%20the%20situation%20in%20Manipur%20was%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInternet%20ban%20and%20bias%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20took%20a%20straightforward%20view%20of%20the%20role%20of%20the%20internet%20ban%20in%20affecting%20cross-checking%20and%20monitoring%20of%20news%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20straight%20%E2%80%9Cmistake%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20surefire%20way%20of%20allowing%20rumours%20to%20float.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternet%20was%20first%20cut%20off%20in%20the%20state%20on%20May%203.%20Several%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-government-extends-internet-shutdown-till-june-30%5C%22%3Eorders%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20since%20then%20called%20for%20its%20continuation%2C%20until%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-internet-restricted-access-mobile-suspended%5C%22%3Erestricted%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20permitted%20in%20late%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20thanks%20to%20this%20breakdown%20of%20communication%2C%20journalists%20effectively%20had%20to%20follow%20the%20government%20narrative%2C%20which%20under%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20%E2%80%9Cbecame%20a%20narrow%20ethnic%20one%20playing%20up%20to%20the%20biases%20of%20the%20majority%20Meitei%20community.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCommunication%20blockade%20by%20the%20government%20had%20a%20deleterious%20effect%20on%20journalism%20as%20it%20directly%20impacted%20the%20ability%20of%20journalists%20to%20communicate%20with%20each%20other%2C%20their%20editors%20and%20their%20sources.%20It%20also%20affected%20the%20media%20because%20local%20news%20gathered%20without%20any%20communication%20links%20was%20not%20sufficient%20to%20give%20a%20balanced%20view%20of%20the%20situation%20and%20often%2C%20even%20that%20was%20not%20enough%20to%20fi%20ll%20their%20pages%20or%20meet%20their%20news%20requirement%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20internet%20ban%20becomes%20absolutely%20necessary%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20then%20news%20platforms%20should%20be%20exempted%20from%20the%20ban%20and%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20media%20representatives%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%20and%20government%20representatives%20should%20monitor%20the%20ban%20and%20its%20duration%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20no%20circumstances%20should%20the%20state%20government%20go%20against%20the%20guidelines%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnuradha%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EBhasin%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%20Manipur%20media%20had%20effectively%20become%20Meitei%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMeitei%20media%2C%20for%20that%20is%20what%20Manipur%20media%20seemed%20to%20have%20become%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%20acted%20collectively%20with%20editors%20consulting%20each%20other%20and%20agreeing%20on%20a%20common%20narrative%20e.g.%2C%20agreeing%20on%20common%20language%20to%20report%20an%20incident%2C%20referring%20to%20certain%20use%20of%20language%20or%20even%20not%20reporting%20an%20event.%20This%20the%20EGI%20team%20was%20told%20was%20because%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20inflame%20the%20already%20volatile%20situation%20further.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20this%20practice%20apparently%20originated%20from%20the%20days%20when%20insurgent%20groups%20were%20active%20in%20the%20Valley%20and%20threatened%20newspaper%20editors%20for%20any%20adverse%20reporting.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20downside%20of%20such%20an%20approach%20during%20ethnic%20violence%20is%20that%20it%20can%20easily%20slip%20into%20forging%20a%20common%20ethnic%20narrative%20and%20lead%20to%20a%20collective%20downslide%20of%20journalistic%20principles%20by%20deciding%20what%20to%20report%20and%20what%20to%20censor.%20This%20seems%20to%20have%20happened%20to%20some%20extent%20during%20the%20present%20cycle%20of%20ethnic%20violence%20between%20the%20Meiteis%20and%20the%20Kukis%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20also%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20indications%20that%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20state%20became%20partisan%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20highlighting%20it%20as%20a%20failure%20of%20performing%20its%20duty%20as%20a%20democratic%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20Meitei%20government%2C%20Meitei%20police%20and%20Meitei%20bureaucracy%20in%20Imphal%20and%20the%20tribal%20people%20living%20in%20the%20Hills%20have%20no%20faith%20in%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFind%20the%20full%20report%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F668684879%2FReport-of-the-fact-finding-mission-on-media-s-reportage-of-the-ethnic-violence-in-Manipur%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20Report%20of%20the%20fact-finding%20mission%20on%20media's%20reportage%20of%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EReport%20of%20the%20fact-finding%20mission%20on%20media%E2%80%99s%20reportage%20of%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22ht