ly%20castigates%20law%20and%20order%20efforts%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbiased%20against%20journalists.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20spokesperson%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20said%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20that%20the%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20(SIA)%2C%20the%20elite%20counter-militancy%20agency%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20%E2%80%9Creserves%20the%20right%20to%20initiate%20further%20legal%20action%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20BBC%20for%20%E2%80%9Cmisreporting%20facts%20in%20a%20case%20which%20is%20sub%20judice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20enquiry%2C%20a%20BBC%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20simply%20say%20that%20the%20BBC%20stands%20by%20its%20journalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20relates%20to%20the%20incarceration%20of%20Fahad%20Shah%2C%20a%20Srinagar-based%20journalist%2C%20for%20publishing%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseditious%E2%80%9D%20article%20authored%20by%20a%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20scholar%2C%20in%20his%20online%20media%20outlet%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20(TKW).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fthe-kashmir-walla-staff-say-website-social-media-blocked%5C%22%3ESrinagar-based%20digital%20media%20house%20shut%20down%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20information%20technology%20ministry%20took%20down%20its%20website%20and%20social%20media%20accounts%20under%20a%20law%20which%20has%20been%20criticised%20by%20the%20free%20speech%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFahad%20Shah%2C%20who%20edited%20a%20digital%20magazine%2C%20was%20arrested%20under%20anti-terror%20laws%20in%20February%202022%2C%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%98propagating%20terror%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20BBC%20said%20in%20its%20report%2C%20the%20only%20reference%20to%20Shah%20in%20the%202165-word%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20didn%E2%80%99t%20clarify%20what%20it%20meant%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmisreporting%20of%20facts%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20BBC%20which%20has%20only%20restated%20the%20charges%20framed%20against%20Shah%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20has%20been%20booked%20in%20four%20anti-terror%20cases%20and%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act.%20While%20he%20has%20got%20bail%20in%20at%20least%20three%20cases%2C%20he%20was%20booked%20by%20the%20SIA%20on%20April%204%2C%202022%20(FIR%20number%2001%2F2022)%2C%20nearly%2011%20years%20after%20his%20digital%20magazine%20hosted%20the%20%E2%80%9Cseditious%E2%80%9D%20article%20titled%20%E2%80%9CThe%20shackles%20of%20slavery%20will%20break%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20was%20authored%20by%20Aala%20Fazili%2C%20a%20research%20scholar%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Pharmaceutical%20Department%2C%20who%20has%20also%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SIA%20filed%20a%20chargesheet%20in%20the%20case%20against%20Shah%20and%20Fazili%20in%20March%20this%20year.%20Shah%20has%20been%20booked%20under%20sections%2035%20(accepting%20foreign%20contribution%20in%20contravention%20of%20provisions%20of%20FCRA)%20and%2039%20(violation%20of%20FCRA)%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%202010%20in%20the%20case%20with%20police%20alleging%20that%20his%20digital%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20subscription%20model%20could%20be%20used%20to%20%E2%80%98foment%20trouble%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20convicted%20in%20these%20four%20cases%2C%20Shah%2C%20who%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20publishing%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20against%20government%20policies%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chaving%20radical%20ideology%20right%20from%20your%20childhood%E2%80%9D%2C%20faces%20different%20sentences%20which%20can%20extend%20to%20life%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BBC%20report%2C%20which%20was%20shared%20widely%20on%20social%20media%2C%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20arrests%20of%20Aasif%20Sultan%2C%20a%20Srinagar-based%20jour