f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsportsbookawards.com%2Fshortlist-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3E2023%20Sports%20Book%20Awards%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20under%20the%20category%20of%20Cricket%20Book%20of%20the%20Year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%20published%20in%20the%20UK%20by%20Polaris%20Publishing%20in%20July%202022%2C%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20Indian%20edition%20was%20brought%20out%20by%20Westland%20Sport%20in%20October%20last%20year.%20Ironically%2C%20it%20is%20still%20not%20available%20in%20Pakistan.%20It%20took%20months%20for%20me%20to%20get%20hold%20of%20a%20copy%2C%20finally%20obtained%20through%20Aisha%20Jalil%20who%20manages%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20at%20Pakistan%20Cricket%20Board.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20348px)%2085vw%2C%20348px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02145516%2F8-Unveiling_Jazbaa_book-cover.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22348%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02145516%2F8-Unveiling_Jazbaa_book-cover.jpg%20764w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02145516%2F8-Unveiling_Jazbaa_book-cover-191x300.jpg%20191w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02145516%2F8-Unveiling_Jazbaa_book-cover-652x1024.jpg%20652w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671183%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22546%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAayush%20Puthran%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EUnveiling%20Jazbaa%3A%20A%20History%20of%20Pakistan%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Cricket%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPolaris%20Publishing%20Limited%20(July%202022)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20the%20writer%20is%20Indian%20and%20male%20makes%20this%20book%20all%20the%20more%20remarkable.%20Puthran%20has%20captured%20not%20just%20the%20state%20of%20the%20sport%20in%20Pakistan%20but%20also%20the%20social%2C%20political%2C%20religious%20and%20administrative%20challenges%20women%20cricketers%20here%20face%20at%20every%20step.%20The%20book%20is%20%E2%80%9Cabout%20so%20much%20more%20than%20cricket%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20acclaimed%20sports%20journalist%20Tim%20Wigmore%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20put%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20the%20first%20few%20chapters%2C%20I%20was%20reminded%20of%20my%20days%20at%20the%20Kinnaird%20Cricket%20Club%2C%20of%20boys%20making%20fun%20of%20the%20girls%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20of%20my%20female%20classmates%20begging%20their%20parents%20to%20let%20them%20play.%20All%20cricket%20news%20on%20television%20and%20all%20discussions%20about%20cricket%20in%20Pakistani%20homes%2C%20offices%2C%20schools%2C%20sports%20clubs%20and%20marketplaces%20had%20one%20underlying%20premise%3A%20that%20it%20is%20a%20sport%20for%20men%2C%20not%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUnveiling%20Jazbaa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20an%20intriguing%20and%20forthright%20%E2%80%98unveiling%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20anger%20and%20passion%2C%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejazbaa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20runs%20in%20every%20female%20cricketer%E2%80%99s%20veins%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20conservative%20environment%20of%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20her%20foreword%20to%20the%20book%2C%20award-winning%20Pakistani-British%20novelist%20and%20columnist%20Kamila%20Shamsie%20describes%20the%201980s%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20worst%20period%20to%20be%20a%20woman%20in%20Pakistan%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20with%20a%20new%20dawn%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20first%20female%20prime%20minister%2C%20Benazir%20Bhutto%2C%20two%20teenage%20girls%2C%20Shaiza%20Khan%20and%20Sharmeen%20Khan%2C%20decided%20to%20fight%20for%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20team.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20made%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20conservative%20culture%2C%20the%20simple%20act%20of%20women%20playing%20cricket%20or%20taking%20decisions%20for%20themselves%20was%20taboo.%20Women%20had%20to%20have%20the%20%E2%80%98audacity%20to%20play%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20writer%20comments%20in%20the%20first%20chapter.%20The%20grounds%20of%20colleges%20like%20Kinnaird%20College%20for%20Women%2C%20besides%20Lahore%20College%20for%20Women%2C%20College%20of%20Home%20Economics%2C%20and%20Government%20Islamia%20College%20for%20Women%20allowed%20women%20to%20play%20some%20cricket%20in%20the%201980s.%20Although%20the%20number%20of%20grounds%20have%20shot%20up%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20Kinnaird%20College%20still%20holds%20a%20large%20number%20of%20tournaments%20in%20Lahore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20General%20Zia-ul-Haq%E2%80%99s%20dictatorship%20setting%20the%20tone%20for%20right-wing%20conservatism%20in%20society%20at%20large%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20barely%20had%20any%20support%20from%20sports%20organisations%20or%20the%20government.%20In%201988%2C%20Jamaat-e-Islami%2C%20a%20right-wing%20political%20party%20opposed%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20women%20playing%20cricket%20at%20a%20larger%20ground%20in%20Karachi%2C%20issued%20death%20threats%20to%20Shaiza%20Khan%20and%20Sharmeen%20Khan.%20That%20did%20not%20stop%20them%2C%20but%20security%20had%20to%20be%20beefed%20up%20at%20the%20venue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20several%20years%2C%20the%20team%20had%20few%20wins%20to%20show%2C%20due%20to%20limited%20grounds%20for%20practice%20and%20lack%20of%20professional%20coaching%20and%20equipment.%20But%20for%20these%20young%20women%2C%20the%20act%20of%20simply%20showing%20up%20was%20more%20significant%20than%20winning%20tournaments.%20They%20had%20to%20let%20the%20world%20know%20that%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20team%20existed%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20be%20able%20to%20play%20cricket%20was%20challenging%20enough%3B%20beating%20top%20international%20sides%20was%20an%20afterthought%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20Puthran.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20also%20describes%20how%20cultural%20exchange%20during%20international%20cricket%20tournaments%20enriched%20not%20just%20the%20Pakistani%20players%20but%20also%20Indians.%20The%20atmosphere%20of%20political%20conflict%20and%20strife%20was%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20affection%20between%20Indian%20and%20Pakistani%20players.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20Asia%20Cup%202006%2C%20the%20Indian%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20team%20travelled%20to%20Karachi%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20to%20play.%20They%20were%20overwhelmed%20with%20the%20hospitality%20they%20received.%20Markets%20were%20cleared%20out%20for%20two%20hours%20to%20let%20them%20shop%2C%20a%20security%20team%20was%20arranged%20for%20them%20at%20all%20hours%2C%20parties%20held%20in%20their%20honour%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENooshin%20Al%20Khadeer%2C%20an%20Indian%20player%2C%20visited%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20elder%20sister%2C%20who%20had%20migrated%20from%20Hyderabad%2C%20India%2C%20to%20Karachi%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20during%20Partition.%20Visa%20restrictions%20had%20kept%20the%20siblings%E2%80%99%20families%20from%20meeting.%20It%20was%20cricket%20that%20gave%20Khadeer%20the%20opportunity%20to%20meet%20her%20aunt%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%202012%20to%202016%2C%20under%20Sana%20Mir%E2%80%99s%20captaincy%20and%20Mohtashim%20Rasheed%E2%80%99s%20coaching%2C%20the%20team%20began%20to%20flourish%20and%20even%20win%20some%20matches.%20A%20sense%20of%20stability%20set%20in%2C%20and%20long%20years%20of%20familiarity%20amongst%20the%20players%20helped%20them%20coordinate%20well.%20Besides%20tournaments%2C%20they%20won%20the%20hearts%20of%20their%20people%20and%20became%20role%20models%20for%20thousands%20of%20women%20in%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20episode%20from%20the%20book%20that%20stands%20out%20is%20about%20fast%20bowler%20Asmavia%20Iqbal%20in%20ICC%20T20%202010.%20She%20was%20sick%20with%20food%20poisoning%20during%20the%20match%2C%20but%20managed%20to%20get%20two%20wickets%20restricting%20South%20Africa%20to%20180%20for%209.%20Her%20triumph%20didn%E2%80%99t%20end%20there.%20When%20it%20was%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20turn%20to%20bat%2C%20the%20scores%20went%20downhill.%20With%20only%20four%20wickets%20left%2C%20Asmavia%20Iqbal%20joined%20Marina%20Iqbal%20on%20the%20pitch.%20Despite%20throwing%20up%20again%20on%20the%20field%2C%20she%20stayed%20put.%20The%20two%20batters%20remained%20till%20the%20end%20and%2C%20braving%20her%20illness%2C%20Asmavia%20scored%20a%20final%20six%20and%20ended%20the%20match%20with%20a%20historic%20win%20for%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20players%20have%20remained%20humble%20and%20hardworking.%20This%20was%20clear%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20Kinnaird%20College.%20One%20day%2C%20my%20sister%20came%20home%20from%20cricket%20practice%20telling%20us%20about%20a%20player%20who%20had%20practised%20alongside%20her%20since%20I%20was%20home%20sick%20that%20day.%20The%20woman%20took%20laps%20around%20the%20field%20with%20my%20sister%20and%20helped%20her%20with%20the%20ball.%20Later%2C%20watching%20the%209%20pm%20news%2C%20my%20sister%20pointed%20to%20the%20television%20screen%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20who%20helped%20me%20today.%E2%80%9D%20It%20was%20Sana%20Mir%20herself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20women%20exerted%20themselves%20nonstop%2C%20they%20gave%20it%20their%20all%20just%20to%20play.%20They%20broke%20the%20barriers%20that%20prevented%20Pakistan%20from%20having%20a%20successful%20women%E2%80%99s%20cricket%20team.%20The%20book%2C%20which%20features%20an%20arresting%20face%20crop%20of%20Sana%20Mir%20on%20the%20cover%2C%20brings%20to%20light%20the%20fearlessness%20of%20these%20women%20and%20how%20they%20forged%20ahead%20despite%20odds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20not%20only%20entered%20a%20%E2%80%98gentleman%E2%80%99s%20sport%E2%80%99%20but%20also%20achieved%20great%20feats%20because%20they%20had%20the%20audacity%20to%20play.%20They%20are%20harbingers%20of%20change%20not%20just%20for%20women%20in%20Pakistan%20but%20the%20world%20over.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENoor%20e%20Emaan%20is%20a%20student%20in%20Lahore%2C%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fsapannews.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESapan%20News%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20syndicated%20feature.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693654249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02145507%2F1-1997-World-Cup-team-photo-credit-PWCCA.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fpassion-to-play-the-outstanding-story-of-womens-cricket-in-pakistan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian%20sports%20journalist%20Aayush%20Puthran%E2%80%99s%20book%20%E2%80%98Unveiling%20Jazbaa%E2%80%99%20spotlights%20the%20daunting%20challenges%20faced%20by%20women%20cricketers%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20making%20their%20victories%20on%20the%20world%20stage%20all%20the%20more%20remarkable%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fpassion-to-play-the-outstanding-story-of-womens-cricket-in-pakistan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Biggest%20celebrity%20breakup%20rumours%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693650600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103289520%2Cimgsize-104844.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes